main event: Two bright white objects were observed in San Jose, California on 29 June 1965.
interesting points: The objects were moving southward and were very close to each other,The objects were described as having a funnel shape and the size of a basketball,Observation noted contrails running from north to south,Weather conditions were clear at the time of the sighting,The sighting lasted approximately three minutes.
witness description: 2nd Lt. William E. Borden, Manual Weapons Controller/Intelligence Officer
